  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_90601448" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/90601448" />
    <a title="Melanie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3195534-melanie"><img alt="Melanie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1477422143p2/3195534.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/90601448?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Melanie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Melanie" href="/user/show/3195534-melanie">Melanie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780425219256" href="/book/show/2206448.Mistress_of_the_Art_of_Death">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3195534-melanie?shelf=mystery-thriller-i-own">mystery-thriller-i-own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer90601448" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13956271377228634272">3.5 stars. I wasn&apos;t sure at the beginning of this book if I would like this. For some reason, I was having trouble comprehending. I&apos;m not even sure if that is an accurate way to describe it. But then it all came together and I really enjoyed the story. Set in the Middle Ages, this book satisfied my historical fiction addiction. I love the premise of there being forensic pathology in that time period (even if it probably isn&apos;t historically accurate) and a woman being the doctor. The &quot;bad guy&quot;, th</span>
  <span id="freeText13956271377228634272" style="display:none">3.5 stars. I wasn't sure at the beginning of this book if I would like this. For some reason, I was having trouble comprehending. I'm not even sure if that is an accurate way to describe it. But then it all came together and I really enjoyed the story. Set in the Middle Ages, this book satisfied my historical fiction addiction. I love the premise of there being forensic pathology in that time period (even if it probably isn't historically accurate) and a woman being the doctor. The "bad guy", the church, the town locals are all great characters. There is some romance which didn't bother me either. I am looking forward to the next installment (which I already have). <br />Recommended if this type of book is your thing :)</span>
  <a data-text-id="13956271377228634272" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


