  <span id="freeText7526057821973665938" style="display:none">It took me some time to read this book cause I've got exams coming up, not because I didn't like it..<br /><br />If you like history books, you will be pleasantly surprised with this book, I mean I liked it and I don't like historical fiction, not even Phillipa Gregory's books. I like how the main character is witty smart, intelligent girl, who is pretty independent considering the time the book was set in. <br />Also, the plot is great, you've got the crime, but not many details about it, which tbh I was glad there wasn't, I dont think I would have been able to read about the gore details. There are many "unbelievable" things that happened in the book, but all in all it's a good book, worth reading, and has some great remarks you'll like! :D<br /><br />Also, I think Sir Rowley Picot was inspired by Rhett Butler, or is it just me? </span>
